title: HTML
about: The HyperText Markup Language or HTML is the standard markup language for documents designed to be displayed in a web browser.

title: CSS
about: Cascading Style Sheets is a style sheet language used for describing the presentation of a document written in a markup language such as HTML or XML.

title: JavaScript
about: JavaScript, often abbreviated to JS, is a programming language that is one of the core technologies of the World Wide Web, alongside HTML and CSS.

title: Bootstrap 5
about: Bootstrap is a free and open-source CSS framework directed at responsive, mobile-first front-end web development.

title: Tailwind CSS
about: The main feature of Tailwind is that, unlike other CSS frameworks, it does not provide a series of predefined classes for elements such as buttons.

title: React JS
about: React is a free and open-source front-end JavaScript library for building user interfaces based on UI components.
